Author:
Vol / Page: 11
Edition:
Quote: St. Patrick's Eve, as Paddy would have it was a great day here. The band from the Royal Concert Hall, together with a number of volunteer performers on violins, flutes, horns, tin cases, dishes, and kerosene tins, paraded the town till long after midnight, serenading the various hotel keepers, the camp, and principal store keepers, who all responded to the honor done them by "shouting" liberally bottles of P.B and square gin as a peace offering to the noisy followers of the patron saint.
